10/11/2004
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- Serbian Prime Minister Vojislav Kostunica reiterated that Belgrade should be included in talks on Kosovo's decentralisation, during a meeting Tuesday (9 November) with a delegation of British lawmakers. He again called on the international community to provide institutional guarantees for minorities in Kosovo. 
Also Tuesday, a delegation of US senators visited Kosovo, meeting with political leaders. They visit Belgrade on Wednesday. (Beta - 10/11/04; B92, Tanjug - 09/11/04) 
